I don't know.

1080
01:10:48,372 --> 01:10:50,406
[ Speaking In Native Language ]

1081
01:10:54,945 --> 01:10:57,313
What's happening?
- The doctor will explain.

1082
01:10:57,354 --> 01:10:59,462
Syracuse, can we talk in private?

1083
01:10:59,499 --> 01:11:00,850
What's going on?

1084
01:11:00,891 --> 01:11:03,720
Alex had a donor card.
- What?

1085
01:11:04,371 --> 01:11:06,255
We have a tissue match.

1086
01:11:06,296 --> 01:11:08,485
Strangest thing, but it's happened.

1087
01:11:08,526 --> 01:11:10,393
Are you serious?

1088
01:11:10,794 --> 01:11:12,362
Come on.

1089
01:11:41,625 --> 01:11:43,593
[ Speaking In Native Language ]

1090
01:11:46,263 --> 01:11:48,632
So why are you here?

1091
01:11:49,533 --> 01:11:51,434
You speak their language now.

1092
01:11:51,835 --> 01:11:53,670
It's softer than ours.

1093
01:11:55,573 --> 01:11:57,506
I wish you were dead.

1094
01:11:57,807 --> 01:12:00,142
None of us are that lucky.

1095
01:12:00,243 --> 01:12:05,141
So, the sea spit you out, did it?

1096
01:12:05,192 --> 01:12:06,983
It can swallow me again.

1097
01:12:07,984 --> 01:12:10,488
We don't belong here, do we?

1098
01:12:11,789 --> 01:12:14,356
- So, go home.

1099
01:12:14,397 --> 01:12:15,658
I can't.

1100
01:12:15,999 --> 01:12:18,360
Police want to talk to me.

1101
01:12:18,431 --> 01:12:20,129
- About what?

1102
01:12:20,190 --> 01:12:24,066
She came from nowhere.
Drunk.

1103
01:12:24,267 --> 01:12:27,269
They should talk to her, not me.
- Tell them that.

1104
01:12:27,310 --> 01:12:28,605
I will.

1105
01:12:28,656 --> 01:12:31,173
And then you'll tell me.

1106
01:12:31,674 --> 01:12:33,175
Nothing.

1107
01:12:49,859 --> 01:12:51,227
Hey.

1108
01:12:52,796 --> 01:12:55,031
Where is mom?

1109
01:12:55,832 --> 01:12:58,367
She's asleep.
She can't see you right now.

1110
01:12:58,568 --> 01:13:00,202
But she will later.

1111
01:13:00,403 --> 01:13:02,138
Where's Ondine?

1112
01:13:02,239 --> 01:13:04,341
Ondine's close by.

1113
01:13:04,642 --> 01:13:06,709
You'll see her, too.

1114
01:13:07,310 --> 01:13:08,545
Just rest.

1115
01:13:08,746 --> 01:13:11,114
Just rest.

1116
01:13:12,715 --> 01:13:15,384
[ ♫ Accordion Playing ♫ ]

1117
01:13:29,566 --> 01:13:33,069
He had a wife
and three children in Scotland.

1118
01:13:33,370 --> 01:13:35,137
Where are they now?

1119
01:13:35,338 --> 01:13:38,174
They said we were welcome to him.

1120
01:13:38,575 --> 01:13:40,376
I'm sorry it happened like this.

1121
01:13:42,579 --> 01:13:44,346
Sure I can't take it in.

1122
01:13:44,397 --> 01:13:45,915
I know.

1123
01:13:46,216 --> 01:13:47,618
It's hard.

1124
01:13:49,319 --> 01:13:51,257
Why aren't you blaming me?

1125
01:13:52,298 --> 01:13:54,857
Because for once
you had nothing to do with it.

1126
01:13:54,958 --> 01:13:57,006
Why do I feel as if I did?

1127
01:13:57,227 --> 01:13:59,028
Because you're Circus.

1128
01:13:59,229 --> 01:14:01,810
You get everything wrong.

1129
01:14:06,136 --> 01:14:08,204
I met him on this ferry.

1130
01:14:09,005 --> 01:14:10,505
Where was I?

1131
01:14:10,646 --> 01:14:12,008
[ Sighs ]

1132
01:14:12,039 --> 01:14:14,144
Where you always were.

1133
01:14:14,745 --> 01:14:16,680
At sea.

1134
01:14:18,991 --> 01:14:21,836
[Sighs]
Take Annie home when she's stronger.

1135
01:14:21,887 --> 01:14:24,486
Till I get out of this thing,
I can't cope.

1136
01:14:24,887 --> 01:14:25,920
Okay.

1137
01:14:26,321 --> 01:14:27,326
It's what you always wanted,
isn't it?

1138
01:14:27,357 --> 01:14:28,864
Yes.

1139
01:14:28,995 --> 01:14:31,588
So, you've got it.

1140
01:14:31,929 --> 01:14:33,996
But I don't want that woman there.

1141
01:14:35,866 --> 01:14:38,067
And take me to his wake now.

1142
01:14:38,168 --> 01:14:40,802
I can't.
- Oh, I insist.

1143
01:14:48,811 --> 01:14:50,412
Two whiskies and ice.

1144
01:14:50,513 --> 01:14:51,347
- One.

1145
01:14:51,448 --> 01:14:52,781
Two.

1146
01:14:52,882 --> 01:14:54,249
Maura, I don't.

1147
01:14:54,331 --> 01:14:56,451
Show some respect.
It's his funeral.

1148
01:15:12,602 --> 01:15:14,336
Get rid of her, Circus.

1149
01:15:14,387 --> 01:15:15,437
- Who?

1150
01:15:15,478 --> 01:15:17,172
Your water baby.

1151
01:15:17,473 --> 01:15:20,342
She brings good luck, then bad.

1152
01:15:45,668 --> 01:15:46,992
Two more, Maggie.

1153
01:15:51,541 --> 01:15:53,609
[ Indistinct Conversations, Laughter ]

1154
01:15:58,448 --> 01:16:00,582
[ Retching ]

1155
01:16:04,454 --> 01:16:06,689
You all right?

1156
01:16:23,906 --> 01:16:25,008
Finders keepers.

1157
01:16:26,009 --> 01:16:28,111
[ Laughing ]

1158
01:16:40,756 --> 01:16:42,318
Why are you looking at me like that?

1159
01:16:42,459 --> 01:16:44,655
Because you're a selkie.

1160
01:16:45,696 --> 01:16:47,123
And I'm an alcoholic.

1161
01:16:48,664 --> 01:16:50,700
A peaceful night's sleep, had you?

1162
01:16:51,735 --> 01:16:53,435
No.

1163
01:16:54,436 --> 01:16:56,771
He's still out there somewhere.

1164
01:16:57,272 --> 01:17:00,209
Okay.
I'm taking you home.

1165
01:17:01,244 --> 01:17:02,277
Hey!

1166
01:17:11,321 --> 01:17:14,190
That bit about the husband...

1167
01:17:14,191 --> 01:17:15,524
He's not my husband.

1168
01:17:15,525 --> 01:17:17,459
What is he, then?

1169
01:17:20,130 --> 01:17:21,899
My pushta.

1170
01:17:23,200 --> 01:17:25,701
What's that?
Selkie for "squeeze"?

1171
01:17:26,402 --> 01:17:27,369
Huh?

1172
01:17:27,401 --> 01:17:29,739
Look. You're home.

1173
01:17:30,240 --> 01:17:31,934
You'll be safe there.

1174
01:17:32,175 --> 01:17:34,209
You can sing your song.

1175
01:17:34,710 --> 01:17:36,025
Who will I sing it to?

1176
01:17:36,056 --> 01:17:37,259
To me.

1177
01:17:37,290 --> 01:17:40,182
Go on, sing!
Make the seals dance!

1178
01:17:40,483 --> 01:17:41,563
I can't.
- Why not?

1179
01:17:41,594 --> 01:17:42,864
Because you're drunk.

1180
01:17:42,895 --> 01:17:44,654
I'll be sober in the morning.

1181
01:17:44,755 --> 01:17:46,258
You can sing to me then.

1182
01:17:46,489 --> 01:17:50,853
I fished round here for years.
Never knew this selkie stuff.

1183
01:17:50,894 --> 01:17:53,828
Jeez, maybe you <i>were</i> dead,
and I fished you back to life.

1184
01:17:53,859 --> 01:17:54,997
Yes!

1185
01:17:55,498 --> 01:17:57,599
And now you're gonna haunt me, huh?

1186
01:17:57,700 --> 01:17:58,801
Forever.

1187
01:17:58,832 --> 01:18:00,302
Come here.

1188
01:18:00,603 --> 01:18:02,901
What does "haunt" mean, huh?

1189
01:18:02,939 --> 01:18:05,274
What does "haunt" mean?
Stop it.

1190
01:18:18,754 --> 01:18:20,255
You want some?

1191
01:18:24,494 --> 01:18:27,562
Selkies don't drink?

1192
01:18:34,404 --> 01:18:37,673
Oh, so you're safe here.

1193
01:18:37,674 --> 01:18:39,809
Is that right?

1194
01:18:42,345 --> 01:18:43,512
How's Annie?

1195
01:18:43,513 --> 01:18:45,281
She's fine.

1196
01:18:53,924 --> 01:18:56,258
She's safe, too.

1197
01:18:58,261 --> 01:19:00,197
I got another bottle on the boat.

1198
01:19:01,998 --> 01:19:03,899
Syracuse.

1199
01:19:05,668 --> 01:19:07,803
What does "haunt" mean?

1200
01:19:07,954 --> 01:19:10,472
- It means what <i>you're</i> doing...

1201
01:19:11,273 --> 01:19:12,609
...to me.

1202
01:19:22,052 --> 01:19:24,453
[ Motor Starts ]

1203
01:19:25,889 --> 01:19:27,857
He wouldn't!

1204
01:19:30,560 --> 01:19:32,928
Syracuse!

1205
01:19:32,929 --> 01:19:34,930
Syracuse!

1206
01:19:36,900 --> 01:19:38,468
- Don't!

1207
01:19:40,737 --> 01:19:41,837
What are you doing?

1208
01:19:41,838 --> 01:19:43,973
I know it's not how fairy tales end.

1209
01:19:44,074 --> 01:19:47,409
But this one does.
This one does because it has to.

1210
01:19:47,450 --> 01:19:50,212
What do you mean?
What do you mean?!

1211
01:19:50,253 --> 01:19:52,748
I mean your kind and my kind.

1212
01:19:53,449 --> 01:19:55,818
We don't belong together.

1213
01:19:55,919 --> 01:19:57,652
[ Crying ]
I have to say good-bye...

1214
01:19:57,693 --> 01:19:58,988
Go away.

1215
01:20:01,489 --> 01:20:02,891
...to Annie.

1216
01:21:44,693 --> 01:21:46,094
Syracuse.

1217
01:22:02,744 --> 01:22:03,912
Hey, buddy.

1218
01:22:03,953 --> 01:22:06,982
Oh, I'm your buddy, am I?

1219
01:22:07,783 --> 01:22:10,220
Yeah. You are.

1220
01:22:11,221 --> 01:22:13,789
You're my sobriety buddy.

1221
01:22:14,790 --> 01:22:17,793
Where were you last night?
I needed you.

1222
01:22:18,394 --> 01:22:20,362
You fell off the wagon.

1223
01:22:20,407 --> 01:22:22,098
- Big time.

1224
01:22:23,899 --> 01:22:25,835
Circus of fools.

1225
01:22:26,336 --> 01:22:29,672
I was twirling around that big top.

1226
01:22:31,140 --> 01:22:32,241
[ Groans ]

1227
01:22:32,742 --> 01:22:35,511
I'm back in the sawdust now.

1228
01:22:36,212 --> 01:22:38,882
And it tastes like shite.

1229
01:22:39,883 --> 01:22:41,850
[ Sighs ]

1230
01:22:44,553 --> 01:22:47,056
Do you know
what my problem is, buddy?

1231
01:22:47,357 --> 01:22:49,924
- You can't take good luck.

1232
01:22:53,196 --> 01:22:55,463
10 out of 10, Sherlock.

1233
01:22:57,066 --> 01:23:00,002
Misery is easy, Syracuse.

1234
01:23:00,303 --> 01:23:02,871
Happiness you have to work at.

1235
01:23:03,472 --> 01:23:05,508
- Why didn't the tree say that?

1236
01:23:05,909 --> 01:23:08,210
Sure, the tree's
not gonna tell you anything.

1237
01:23:14,183 --> 01:23:15,683
What about the girl?

1238
01:23:16,684 --> 01:23:18,320
- Ah, she's gone.

1239
01:23:18,391 --> 01:23:20,155
And Annie?

1240
01:23:20,456 --> 01:23:22,524
- She's getting out today.

1241
01:23:22,825 --> 01:23:25,027
I'm taking her home with me.

1242
01:23:25,088 --> 01:23:29,097
After that, there's no excuses,
is there, buddy?

1243
01:23:30,599 --> 01:23:32,301
- No.

1244
01:23:33,702 --> 01:23:35,637
Why are you crying?

1245
01:23:35,678 --> 01:23:36,751
- I'm not.

1246
01:23:36,792 --> 01:23:38,753
Yes, you are.
I can tell.

1247
01:23:38,794 --> 01:23:43,511
Maybe because you're back
on the road again. You're home.

1248
01:23:43,912 --> 01:23:45,447
Where's Ondine?

1249
01:23:45,488 --> 01:23:48,043
- Ondine had to go away for a while.

1250
01:23:48,084 --> 01:23:51,686
That's why you're crying.
- It's not, I swear.

1251
01:23:51,987 --> 01:23:54,056
Did her husband come?

1252
01:23:54,257 --> 01:23:55,523
- He must have.

1253
01:23:55,724 --> 01:23:58,293
Because she's gone...
On sea business.

1254
01:23:58,334 --> 01:23:59,694
[ Laughs ]

1255
01:23:59,695 --> 01:24:02,164
But she'll be back, you know.
- Do you think?

1256
01:24:02,165 --> 01:24:05,367
I know.
She left something here.

1257
01:24:05,368 --> 01:24:07,035
What?

1258
01:24:08,838 --> 01:24:11,440
Woman On Television:
"<i>The eldest of two children,
a younger brother, Robert...</i>"

1259
01:24:11,491 --> 01:24:13,375
[ Channel Changes ]

1260
01:24:15,878 --> 01:24:17,312
What time is it?

1261
01:24:17,813 --> 01:24:18,851
Half-one.

1262
01:24:19,892 --> 01:24:21,183
Why didn't you wake me?

1263
01:24:21,484 --> 01:24:23,852
Because you were sleeping like a baby.

1264
01:24:24,553 --> 01:24:26,248
I thought you were the baby.

1265
01:24:26,289 --> 01:24:28,123
Doesn't look like it.

1266
01:24:28,424 --> 01:24:30,693
[ Groans ]

1267
01:24:31,094 --> 01:24:32,654
Do you want breakfast?

1268
01:24:32,695 --> 01:24:34,062
Lunch.

1269
01:24:38,167 --> 01:24:40,102
There you are, baby.

1270
01:24:43,906 --> 01:24:51,079
♫ Singing in silence ♫

1271
01:24:53,082 --> 01:25:03,392
♫ let's sing into the years,
like one ♫

1272
01:25:05,594 --> 01:25:06,794
[ Channel Changes ]

1273
01:25:06,795 --> 01:25:09,331
Annie, that song...
- What song?

1274
01:25:09,372 --> 01:25:10,765
Just a minute ago.

1275
01:25:13,369 --> 01:25:19,341
♫ a sound for no one ♫

1276
01:25:19,382 --> 01:25:20,775
It's real.

1277
01:25:20,816 --> 01:25:22,757
'Course it's real.
It's Sigur Ros.

1278
01:25:22,798 --> 01:25:27,649
♫ let's sing in tune ♫

1279
01:25:27,650 --> 01:25:33,588
♫ but now it's home ♫

1280
01:25:38,428 --> 01:25:40,596
Annie, I have to go out for a bit.

1281
01:25:41,097 --> 01:25:43,431
I'll take you to your mom's.
- No.

1282
01:25:43,482 --> 01:25:45,233
I can't leave you on your own.

1283
01:25:45,334 --> 01:25:47,385
Yes, you can.
Don't you get it? I'm better.

1284
01:25:47,436 --> 01:25:48,608
Are you sure?

1285
01:25:49,539 --> 01:25:52,508
You got some unfinished sea business?

1286
01:25:53,309 --> 01:25:55,144
I suppose.

1287
01:25:55,845 --> 01:25:57,563
Go on, then.

1288
01:25:57,714 --> 01:26:00,401
I'm kind of busy here anyway.

1289
01:26:01,751 --> 01:26:02,952
[ Door Closes ]

1290
01:26:03,253 --> 01:26:04,455
[ Sighs ]

1291
01:26:06,756 --> 01:26:13,161
♫ I wanted to know ♫

1292
01:26:16,666 --> 01:26:22,003
♫ what I have done ♫

1293
01:26:26,008 --> 01:26:27,176
Hey !

1294
01:26:27,577 --> 01:26:32,314
♫ I wanted to know ♫

1295
01:26:32,315 --> 01:26:35,918
♫ it's bad ♫

1296
01:26:40,222 --> 01:26:47,896
♫ I wanted to know ♫

1297
01:26:47,937 --> 01:26:49,765
Hey! Hey!

1298
01:26:49,796 --> 01:26:55,471
♫ what I have done ♫

1299
01:26:59,175 --> 01:27:05,113
♫ I wanted to know ♫

1300
01:27:05,114 --> 01:27:09,084
♫ right now ♫

1301
01:27:20,329 --> 01:27:24,766
Ondine: There were seals
down there basking on the rocks.

1302
01:27:24,797 --> 01:27:26,502
My kind, huh?

1303
01:27:26,703 --> 01:27:28,203
I didn't say that.

1304
01:27:28,304 --> 01:27:30,906
No, but you thought it.

1305
01:27:33,910 --> 01:27:36,012
Then the storm came up.

1306
01:27:37,213 --> 01:27:40,116
They slipped into the water,
one by one.

1307
01:27:40,517 --> 01:27:42,951
I was going to join them.

1308
01:27:47,390 --> 01:27:49,258
What changed your mind?

1309
01:27:50,999 --> 01:27:53,328
What changed yours?

1310
01:27:57,066 --> 01:28:01,003
She was switching channels
on the TV...

1311
01:28:02,304 --> 01:28:03,805
and your song came on.

1312
01:28:04,106 --> 01:28:05,974
It was never my song.

1313
01:28:08,790 --> 01:28:09,778
So tell me.

1314
01:28:10,079 --> 01:28:12,849
No. No.
Take me home.

1315
01:28:13,550 --> 01:28:14,763
Where is home?

1316
01:28:14,794 --> 01:28:16,618
What do you think?

1317
01:28:18,521 --> 01:28:20,503
You'll tell me the truth now.

1318
01:28:21,544 --> 01:28:22,740
The truth?

1319
01:28:24,781 --> 01:28:27,175
The truth is I'm a creature from the sea

1320
01:28:27,196 --> 01:28:29,635
that found her seal coat and buried it

1321
01:28:29,666 --> 01:28:31,499
because she found a family she liked.

1322
01:28:31,530 --> 01:28:33,006
Please.

1323
01:28:34,047 --> 01:28:35,638
That's...

1324
01:28:37,239 --> 01:28:39,275
That's one truth.

1325
01:28:39,676 --> 01:28:41,994
You don't want to know the other.

1326
01:28:44,512 --> 01:28:45,914
Try me.

1327
01:28:47,850 --> 01:28:49,151
Okay.

1328
01:28:52,655 --> 01:28:56,958
I am a prisoner
and a drug mule from Romania.

1329
01:28:57,359 --> 01:28:59,061
I said the real truth.

1330
01:29:03,365 --> 01:29:05,269
This is the real truth.

1331
01:29:06,970 --> 01:29:10,939
I was on a boat with
a kilo of heroin in a backpack.

1332
01:29:11,240 --> 01:29:13,809
Coast guards came,
Vladic made me swim for it.

1333
01:29:13,990 --> 01:29:14,997
Vladic?

1334
01:29:16,278 --> 01:29:17,947
My selkie husband.

1335
01:29:18,648 --> 01:29:20,216
My pushta.

1336
01:29:23,086 --> 01:29:32,460
♫ maybe this time tomorrow ♫

1337
01:29:32,461 --> 01:29:37,833
♫ or it may be today ♫

1338
01:29:42,672 --> 01:29:45,654
Ondine: <i>He was like
a monster from a fairytale.</i>

1339
01:29:45,695 --> 01:29:48,957
<i>But he couldn't swim.</i>

1340
01:29:48,998 --> 01:29:51,946
<i>So he made me take to the water.</i>

1341
01:29:53,282 --> 01:29:56,084
<i>I was always a good swimmer,</i>

1342
01:29:56,285 --> 01:29:59,387
<i>But your Irish waves wore me down.</i>

1343
01:30:00,990 --> 01:30:03,491
<i>I swam till I could swim no more.</i>

1344
01:30:05,161 --> 01:30:08,764
<i>Then I floated.</i>

1345
01:30:08,765 --> 01:30:10,866
<i>Then I sank.</i>

1346
01:30:13,703 --> 01:30:16,337
<i>It was almost a relief.</i>

1347
